A certificate of existence shall set forth:
The entity's real name;
That the entity was duly organized under the laws of this Commonwealth, the date of its organization, and the period of its duration if less than perpetual;
That no articles of dissolution, statement of cancellation, or document of similar import is effective;
That all fees, taxes, and penalties owed to this Commonwealth have been paid, if:
Payment is reflected in the records of the Secretary of State; and
Nonpayment affects the existence of the entity;
That its most recent annual report required by KRS 14A.6-010 or predecessor law has been filed by the Secretary of State; and
Subject to KRS 14A.2-120(3), other facts of record in the office of the Secretary of State that may be requested by the applicant.

This section shall not apply to:
Partnerships organized pursuant to KRS Chapter 362 or 362.1;
Limited partnerships other than those subject to KRS Chapter 362.2;
Business trusts governed as to their internal affairs by KRS Chapter 386; or
An individual series of a series entity.
